Interview Questions
1. What are access modifiers in Java, what are their types, and what is their purpose?
-->Access modifiers define visibility (who can access a class, method, variable, or constructor).
    👉 Types:
    public → accessible everywhere
    protected → within package + subclasses
    default (no modifier) → within same package
    private → within same class only
    
    👉 Purpose:
    Control access
    Achieve encapsulation
    Improve security and maintainability



2. Which access modifiers are allowed for top-level classes, and why can't a top-level class be protected or
private?
-->👉 Allowed:
      
      public
      default (no modifier)
      
      ❌ Not allowed:
      
      private
      protected
      
      👉 Reason:
      
      Top-level classes are not members of another class
      private and protected are meant for members (inside classes)
      A top-level class must be accessible either:
      within package (default)
      everywhere (public)



